SIMPLE: informal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Informal
<hw>In*form"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>formal</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not in
the regular, usual, or established form; not according to official,
conventional, prescribed, or customary forms or rules; irregular; hence,
without ceremony; <as>as, an <ex>informal</ex> writing, proceeding, or
visit</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deranged in mind; out of one's senses.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These poor <qex>informal</qex> women.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Informality</ent>⟦br⟧
